        <mxCell id="d1qDQasMmmVKYZnUmQSg-19" parent="1" style="rounded=0;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#9673a6;textShadow=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;container=0;autosize=0;overflow=hidden;" value="INCOMPLETE ARCHITECTURE HERE:&lt;br&gt;MEMORY REFRESHER: case 5 opens a much bigger design question than it first appeared. A fact like “Mario has 4 children” looks simple, but it forces you to decide whether the new thing should become a first-class entity, a plain field, or a deferred unresolved concept. At that point, you will need to think about linked-entity detection, retrieval, disambiguation, duplication avoidance, and relationship modeling. You will also need to decide when a linked entity should follow the same retrieve-resolve-clarify pipeline as subjects, and when it is safe to create it directly. In other words, this branch is really the doorway from a single-entity `UserProfile` memory system into a more relational memory model, so when you return here, treat it as a schema and identity problem, not just as a small routing detail.&lt;br&gt;QUESTIONS TO ANSWER WITH A FULL WORKFLOW HERE:&lt;br&gt;Yes, it’s too simple for the full architecture.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Future questions to capture:&lt;br&gt;- When should a new mention become a first-class entity vs just a field on an existing object?&lt;br&gt;- How do we detect that the “new entity” may already exist under another name?&lt;br&gt;- When do we need entity disambiguation before creating a linked entity?&lt;br&gt;- What identity signals are enough to create a new linked entity safely?&lt;br&gt;- Should linked entities use the same retrieve-resolve-disambiguate pipeline as subjects?&lt;br&gt;- How should relationships be represented between subject and linked entity?&lt;br&gt;- How do we handle partial linked-entity information?&lt;br&gt;- How do we avoid duplicate linked entities over time?&lt;br&gt;- When should we interrupt the user for clarification vs defer the fact?&lt;br&gt;- How should schema evolution happen when linked entities appear repeatedly?&lt;br&gt;- How should non-person entities and linked entities differ architecturally?&lt;br&gt;- When do derived effects on subjects happen after updating a non-subject entity?" vertex="1">
