        <mxCell id="HBjxxj-PaKMHTgiMZ76c-22" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;overflow=hidden;" value="&lt;div&gt;When you return to this part of the architecture, remember that a robust concurrent design should not keep one giant graph execution open while many subject-level branches try to finish and rejoin. The safer design is to let one orchestration graph analyze the user message, identify subjects and facts, resolve what can be resolved, and emit durable item-level tasks such as `update existing subject`, `create new subject`, or `ask user to clarify unresolved subject`. Each of those tasks should then be processed independently so that one slow, ambiguous, or broken item never blocks the rest. In other words, concurrency and fault isolation come from turning one message into many durable work items, not from keeping many live branches inside one run.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The implementation options are mainly about where the task queue lives and how workers are started. The simplest option is an application-managed task table or queue in your own storage layer, where the orchestrator writes tasks and a separate worker process polls and runs the worker graph on each task. A more LangGraph-native option is to keep the task definitions in persistent state and have an external loop or service invoke the worker graph once per task, passing the task payload as input. In both cases, the worker graph does not literally “invoke itself” from inside the same run; instead, some outer orchestrator, scheduler, queue consumer, or application service starts a new graph run for each task. The key idea is that self-reinvocation is replaced by durable task emission plus external task consumption.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="130" width="360" x="605" y="878" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="HBjxxj-PaKMHTgiMZ76c-23" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;validate&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 11px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Proposal validator&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Input: subject/action proposals&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Output: valid proposals or proposal errors&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;- did we miss a subject?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;- is each identity/action decision justified?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;- should any subject move from ignore to create/update?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Output: validated proposals or repair needed&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
